<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1938-12-07T10:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1938-12-07T10:00:00-05:00" n="834" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d834">
                    <note rend="inline" type="source">840.48 Refugees/1058: Telegram</note>
                    <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Kennedy</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                    <opener>
                        <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1938-12-07T15:00:00+00:00">December 7, 1938—3
                            p.m.</date><lb/>[Received December 7—11:55 a.m.]</dateline>
                    </opener>
                    <p>1403. From Rublee. We have been informed that the Brussels meeting with Pell
                        and Cotton tomorrow has been canceled. Preliminary information received
                        through our German intermediary here is that there were too many cooks; that
                        the French had taken up the general problem and specific financial points
                        with Ribbentrop; and that the latter had been obliged to take a position.
                        [Rublee.]</p>
                    <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Kennedy</hi></signed></closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>